      "contentText": "Divemaster (Pro) 4 to 6 weeks &bull; From &#8369;67,500 Who hasn't dreamed of sharing their passion by guiding divers from around the world while living to the rhythm of the ocean? The Divemaster course is your gateway into the professional world of scuba diving. Who hasn't dreamed of sharing their passion by guiding divers from around the world while living to the rhythm of the ocean? The Divemaster course is your gateway into the professional world of scuba diving. We offer an immersive and comprehensive experience that goes far beyond a theoretical program. You'll become part of our team and gain hands-on experience through regular diving. You'll discover the real-world responsibilities of guides and instructors&mdash;managing group safety and anticipating situations underwater and on land. The experience you gain alongside our professionals will expose you to various approaches, help you develop your skills, and shape your own professional identity. What to expect: Supervision, leadership, briefings/debriefings Handling a group and their safety Planning and organization Customer relations and interpersonal skills Overview of dive center operations Duration 4 to 6 weeks Minimum age 18 years old Prerequisites Diver Stress and Rescue, Deep Diving and Enriched Air Nitrox specialty Proof of experience in: navigation, night and limited visibility Minimum 60 logged dives (40 hours) Certification Dive Master Price &#8369;67,500 SSI Divemaster Divemaster professional course",
