      "contentText": "Open Water Instructor 2 weeks &bull; &#8369;140,000 Who hasn&rsquo;t dreamed of turning their passion into a career by teaching and inspiring divers from around the world while living in sync with the sea? Who hasn&rsquo;t dreamed of turning their passion into a career by teaching and inspiring divers from around the world while living in sync with the sea? The SSI Instructor Training Course is the next step into becoming a true educator and leader in the professional diving world. This course goes far beyond learning how to teach from a manual. Over two intensive weeks, you&rsquo;ll be fully immersed in the instructor mindset, working closely with our team through workshops, simulations, and practical teaching exercises. You&rsquo;ll practice confined water, open water, and classroom presentations in realistic scenarios designed to prepare you for real-world teaching. Through hands-on training, role-playing, and mentorship, you&rsquo;ll refine your demonstration quality, presentation skills, and problem-solving abilities. This focused experience will help you build confidence, structure your teaching approach, and develop your own professional instructor identity&mdash;ready for your first students after certification. What to expect: In-water teaching techniques and demonstrations Academic presentations and knowledge development Confined and open water teaching scenarios Student supervision, safety, and problem management Training on professional communication and roles as an instructor Great preparation for successful Instructor Examination (IE) Duration 2 weeks Minimum age 18 years old Prerequisites Dive Master; Enriched air nitrox specialty; Open Water Diver for at least 6 months Certification Open Water Instructor Price &#8369;140,000 Open Water Instructor course",
